text: Pointe à la Hache ( ) is a census-designated place (CDP) and unincorporated community in Plaquemines Parish, Louisiana, United States. "Census 2000 Data for the State of Louisiana" (town list), US Census Bureau, May 2003, webpage: C2000-LA. Located on the east bank of the Mississippi River, the village has been the seat for Plaquemines Parish. As of the 2020 census, its population was 183. ==References== Category:Parish seats in Louisiana Category:Unincorporated communities in Louisiana Category:Census-designated places in Louisiana Category:Settlements in Plaquemines Parish, Louisiana
